At Independence's incorporation, the Utah Population Estimates Committee produced an official population estimate of 117.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.governor.utah.gov/DEA/subcountyestimates.html|title=GOPB DEA Sub County Estimates |website=governor.utah.gov|publisher=Governor's Office of Planning and Budget – State of Utah|year=2008|access-date=September 29, 2009|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090901214154/http://governor.utah.gov/dea/subcountyestimates.html|archive-date=September 1, 2009|via=[[Internet Archive|web.archive.org]]}}</ref> Many of the residents live on land that has been in their families for generations.<ref name="no"/>

As of the census of 2010, there were 164 people living in the town.<ref name="census">{{cite web|url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US4937690|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212141954/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US4937690|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 12, 2020|title=American FactFinder|website=factfinder2.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date=July 20, 2012}}</ref> There were 66 housing units. The [[Race and ethnicity in the United States Census|racial makeup]] of the town was 98.2% White, 0.6% Asian, 0.6% from some other race, and 0.6% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 9.8% of the population.

